ata-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_7423162\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juni 29, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104qnz1719684290999.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qnz1719684290999.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qnz1719684290999.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"mqp1665702922820\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Adding Redundant Relationships\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"mqp1665702922820__adding_redundant_relationships_140472\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">One possibility to improve the performance of the user view is to add a new relationship. Adding a new relationship can shorten an access path, but it might require extra I/O to keep the database consistent.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mqp1665702922820__p_d45884e1_d45885e1_d45886e1\">For example, a user view that shows the materials in a configuration is important for the business. A new relationship, 'MATERIAL is from PART', is added to the relational data model, as shown in the following illustration:</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"mqp1665702922820__fig_d45887e1_d45888e1_d45889e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Adding Redundant Relationships</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Adding redundant relationships\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/addingredundantrelationships.jpg?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mqp1665702922820__p_d45893e1_d45894e1_d45895e1\">The new relationship makes the access path from CONFIGURATION to MATERIAL considerably shorter because the MATERIAL_ID attribute is stored redundantly in the entity PART. Extra I/O is required to keep the database consistent when maintaining a PART.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"mqp1665702922820__fig_d45896e1_d45897e1_d45898e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 2. </span>New Access Profile and Frames-Within-Frames Using Added Relationship</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"New access profile and frames-within-frames using added relationship\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/addedrelationshipaccessprofile.jpg?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mqp1665702922820__p_d45902e1_d45903e1_d45904e1\">The following table shows the amended access profiles:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"4\" id=\"mqp1665702922820__table_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Access Profile Statistics for Added Relationship</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mqp1665702922820__table_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1__entry__1\">\n Access path\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mqp1665702922820__table_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1__entry__2\">\n Via\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mqp1665702922820__table_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1__entry__3\">\n Selected Occurrences (avg.)\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mqp1665702922820__table_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1__entry__4\">\n Access Stress Value\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mqp1665702922820__table_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1__entry__1\">\n &gt;Configuration\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mqp1665702922820__table_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1__entry__2\">\n configuration_id\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mqp1665702922820__table_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1__entry__3\">\n 1\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mqp1665702922820__table_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1__entry__4\">\n 1\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mqp1665702922820__table_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1__entry__1\">\n Configuration&gt;&gt;Part\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mqp1665702922820__table_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1__entry__2\">\n configuration_id\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mqp1665702922820__table_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1__entry__3\">\n 5\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mqp1665702922820__table_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1__entry__4\">\n 5\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mqp1665702922820__table_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1__entry__1\">\n Part&gt;Material\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mqp1665702922820__table_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1__entry__2\">\n material_id\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mqp1665702922820__table_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1__entry__3\">\n 1\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mqp1665702922820__table_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1__entry__4\">\n 5\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"3\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mqp1665702922820__table_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1__entry__1 mqp1665702922820__table_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1__entry__2 mqp1665702922820__table_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1__entry__3\">\n                     Total Access Stress Rating\n                  </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"mqp1665702922820__table_d4388e1_d4389e1_d4390e1__entry__4\">\n 11\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7423162\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7423162\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Adding Redundant Relationships Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juni 29, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Adding Redundant Relationships One possibility to improve the performance of the user view is to add a new relationship. Adding a new relationship can shorten an access path, but it might require extra I/O to keep the database consistent. For example, a user view that shows the materials in a configuration is important for the business. A new relationship, 'MATERIAL is from PART', is added to the relational data model, as shown in the following illustration: Figure 1. Adding Redundant Relationships The new relationship makes the access path from CONFIGURATION to MATERIAL considerably shorter because the MATERIAL_ID attribute is stored redundantly in the entity PART. Extra I/O is required to keep the database consistent when maintaining a PART. Figure 2. New Access Profile and Frames-Within-Frames Using Added Relationship The following table shows the amended access profiles: Table 1. Access Profile Statistics for Added Relationship Access path Via Selected Occurrences (avg.) Access Stress Value >Configuration configuration_id 1 1 Configuration>>Part configuration_id 5 5 Part>Material material_id 1 5 Total Access Stress Rating 11 Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}